      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-7">
            <div class="text-block mb-50">
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20 font-weight-bold color-secondary">
                State-of-the-Art Endoscopy Unit
              </p>
              <div class="video-banner-layout3 bg-overlay mb-50">
                <img src="/assets/images/banners/8.jpg" alt="Endoscopy Services" loading="lazy" width="800" height="450">
                <a class="video__btn video__btn-white popup-video" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nrJtHemSPW4">
                  <div class="video__player">
                    <i class="fa fa-play"></i>
                  </div>
                </a>
              </div><!-- /.video-banner -->
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Our endoscopy unit at the South Asian Liver Institute is equipped with the latest high-definition endoscopes and imaging technology. This allows for precise and detailed examination of the gastrointestinal tract, aiding in the accurate diagnosis of various conditions affecting the esophagus, stomach, intestines, and bile ducts.
              </p>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                We offer a wide range of therapeutic procedures, including removal of polyps, treatment for bleeding, and placement of stents. Our minimally invasive techniques ensure patient comfort, safety, and a quicker recovery time.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Upper GI Endoscopy (Esophagogastroduodenoscopy - EGD)</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Upper endoscopy examines the esophagus, stomach, and duodenum. It is used to diagnose and treat conditions such as:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li>Esophageal varices (enlarged veins) in cirrhosis patients</li>
                <li>Gastritis, ulcers, and gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)</li>
                <li>Celiac disease and malabsorption disorders</li>
                <li>Upper GI bleeding</li>
                <li>Swallowing difficulties</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                <strong>Variceal Band Ligation:</strong> For cirrhosis patients, we perform endoscopic banding to prevent or treat bleeding from esophageal varices. This life-saving procedure places rubber bands around enlarged veins to stop bleeding.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Endoscopic Retrograde Cholangiopancreatography (ERCP)</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                ERCP is a specialized endoscopic procedure that combines endoscopy and X-ray to diagnose and treat problems in the bile ducts and pancreatic duct. Common indications include:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li>Bile duct stones (choledocholithiasis)</li>
                <li>Biliary strictures (narrowing)</li>
                <li>Bile duct tumors</li>
                <li>Pancreatitis</li>
                <li>Bile leaks after surgery</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                During ERCP, we can remove stones, place stents to relieve obstruction, take tissue samples, and perform sphincterotomy to widen the bile duct opening. ERCP requires sedation and is performed by experienced gastroenterologists.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Endoscopic Ultrasound (EUS)</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                EUS combines endoscopy with ultrasound imaging, allowing detailed visualization of the liver, pancreas, bile ducts, and lymph nodes. EUS is particularly useful for:
              </p>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li>Staging liver and pancreatic cancers</li>
                <li>Evaluating pancreatic cysts and tumors</li>
                <li>Detecting small bile duct stones</li>
                <li>Guiding fine needle aspiration (FNA) of masses</li>
                <li>Assessing portal hypertension</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                EUS-guided biopsies provide tissue diagnosis with high accuracy, often avoiding the need for surgical biopsy.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Colonoscopy</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Colonoscopy examines the large intestine (colon) and is important for colorectal cancer screening, especially in patients with liver disease who may have increased cancer risk. We perform diagnostic colonoscopy, polyp removal, and treatment of colonic bleeding.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Capsule Endoscopy</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                For small bowel examination, we offer wireless capsule endoscopy where patients swallow a pill-sized camera that takes thousands of images as it passes through the digestive tract. This non-invasive test helps diagnose small bowel bleeding, Crohn's disease, and tumors.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Patient Preparation and Safety</h5>
              <p class="text-block__desc mb-20">
                Most endoscopic procedures are performed under conscious sedation for patient comfort. Pre-procedure fasting is required. Our endoscopy unit follows strict infection control protocols with automated scope reprocessing. Patients are monitored in our recovery area until fully awake, usually 1-2 hours. Detailed instructions for preparation and post-procedure care are provided.
              </p>
              <h5 class="text-block__title mb-20">Why Choose SALi for Endoscopy?</h5>
              <ul class="list-items list-unstyled mb-40 pl-40">
                <li>Experienced gastroenterologists specializing in liver diseases</li>
                <li>Latest high-definition endoscopic equipment</li>
                <li>Comprehensive diagnostic and therapeutic capabilities</li>
                <li>Same-day procedures with minimal wait times</li>
                <li>Dedicated endoscopy unit with trained nursing staff</li>
                <li>Integrated with our liver transplant and hepatology programs</li>
              </ul>
